            "content": "{\n  \"buggy_files\": [\"drivers/ata/libata-core.c\"],\n  \"buggy_functions\": [\"ata_device_blacklist\", \"ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv\"],\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"reasoning\": \"The Samsung 860 EVO SSD is missing from the ata_device_blacklist array with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag. Currently, Samsung SSD 840* (line 4562) and 850* (line 4564) have this flag to disable queued TRIM, but 860 EVO does not. Without this flag, the device enables queued TRIM operations which cause timeout issues on this SSD model, as evidenced by the SEND FPDMA QUEUED timeout errors in the bug report. The ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv() function (line 2197) checks for this horkage flag at line 2218 and only disables queued TRIM if the flag is present. The fix requires adding a 'Samsung SSD 860*' entry with ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM | ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM after the 850* entry in the ata_device_blacklist array.\"\n}\n",
